@startuml ThrobberAnimator Lifecycle States
!theme plain
title "ThrobberAnimator - State Machine Lifecycle"

[*] --> Created: ThrobberAnimator::new()

Created: active = false\nindex = 0\nthread_handle = None

Created --> Running: start()
note on link
  Idempotent check:
  if active.load(SeqCst) { return; }

  Then:
  - Reset index to 0
  - Set active to true
  - Spawn animation thread
end note

Running: active = true\nindex >= 0\nthread_handle = Some(JoinHandle)
note right of Running
  Animation thread running:
  loop {
    sleep(100ms)
    if active.load(Relaxed) {
      index.fetch_add(1, Relaxed)
    }
  }

  Render thread reading:
  index.load(Relaxed) % symbols.len()
  → symbol()
end note

Running --> Stopped: stop()
note on link
  Sets active to false (SeqCst)
  Animation thread will exit
  within ~100ms
end note

Running --> Running: start() [no-op]
note on link
  If already running,
  start() is idempotent
  (early return)
end note

Stopped: active = false\nindex = N\nthread_handle = Some(JoinHandle)
note right of Stopped
  Animation thread exited
  (waiting for join in Drop)

  symbol() returns "~"
  is_running() returns false
end note

Stopped --> Dropped: Drop::drop()
note on link
  stop() called again (idempotent)
  Join animation thread
  Clean up resources
end note

Dropped: [cleanup]

note over Created, Running
  Start Flow:
  1. User enters natural language query
  2. state.mode = WaitingLLM
  3. state.start_throbber()
     → throbber.start() called
  4. Animation thread spawned
  5. Render loop displays symbol
end note

note over Running, Stopped
  Running Flow:
  - Main thread: render(state)
    - Checks mode == WaitingLLM
    - Checks throbber.is_running()
    - Calls throbber.symbol()
  - Animation thread: increments index
  - Happens ~10 times per second
  - Smooth animation visible in prompt
end note

note over Stopped, Dropped
  Stop Flow:
  1. LLM query completes
  2. orchestrator.handle_query_result()
  3. state.stop_throbber()
     → throbber.stop() called
  4. active flag set to false
  5. Animation thread detects and exits
  6. Final render shows "|~|" prompt
  7. Terminal ready for next input
end note

note over Created, Dropped
  Error/Cancellation Flow:
  - If user presses Ctrl+C
  - cancel_token fires
  - orchestrator exits select! loop
  - state.stop_throbber() called
  - Animation stops gracefully
  - state.mode = Normal
  - Final render shows prompt
end note

state Dropped {
}

@enduml
